<title>UK: Friends Provident to sell Preferred Direct - FT.</title>
<headline>Friends Provident to sell Preferred Direct - FT.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-07-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>British mutual insurer Friends Provident is to sell its Preferred Direct motor insurance arm, Thursday's Financial Times said.</p>
<p>It said Friends Provident was in talks with several potential buyers.</p>
<p>Preferred Direct, which was the first company to begin selling car insurance by telephone in Britain, lost 13 million pounds on sales of 63 million pounds last year, the FT said.</p>
